  "text": "Thus, knowledge of the real and imaginary parts of the Clausius-Mossotti factor predicts the electrokinetic behavior of the particle. For the rest of the paper, we focus on calculating this factor for a semiconducting sphere in the electrolyte. Notice that we do not take into account any induced charge electroosmotic (ICEO) flow, which might affect the dielectrophoretic behavior at low frequencies of the applied field. However, experiments with metal spheres show that the influence of ICEO flow is small [CITATION_1] , and thus, the DEP motion is mainly driven by the forces on the induced particle dipole.",
